100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On November 1, 1925, the British government announced plans to establish a new air route to India, aiming to strengthen trade and travel links across the Empire. In the United States, the Scopes Trial's aftermath continued to stir debate, as educational reforms regarding the teaching of evolution faced opposition in several states. Meanwhile, in Paris, the International Bureau of Weights and Measures released a report advocating for the adoption of the metric system across Europe.
